Text: RE PRS Meeting Agendasmith PST Don At TX Set there was a discussion on this subject and several TX SET representatives will be attending this meeting as well as some TTPT members I have noted the names in the TX Set agenda notes If you would like to know anymore information please feel free to contact me Thanks Rita Morales Exolink Corporation wk cell u Original Message From DonBender mailtoDonBender Sent Wednesday January AM To Subject PRS Meeting Agenda This forwarded note announces Protocol Revision Subcommittees next meeting which is scheduled for January at ERCOT Met Center The first agenda items deal with pending Protocol Revision Requests Two PRRs impact the Retail Market Unexecutable and Estimating Usage Applied to Profiles The ninth agenda item is for PRS to begin prioritizing systems changes This is a critical activity in defining what changes will be in v release Brenda Crockett and I are actively working on having RMS representation at this meeting We hope to have information for you before the end of this week This certainly does not preclude any market participant attending this meeting Brenda and I feel the coordination between PRS and RMS is very critical at this junction that we what assigned representation at these meetings Don Bender Net Phone Phone Net Fax Fax Cell Phone Email Forwarded by Donald G BenderAEPIN on AM Flores Isabel PM To PRS Protocol Revisions Sub cc ERCOT Managers Saathoff Kent Green Jim Subject PRS Meeting Agenda All Attached is the PRS agenda for the meeting days prioritizing System Changes will take place after PRRs are reviewed on and on Please RSVP with Terri Waggoner at if you plan to attend PRS Mtg Agendadoc thank you Isabel Flores Contract Analyst direct fax Confidentiality Notice The information contained in this email message and any documents attached is privileged and confidential and is intended only for the use of the addressee Nothing in this email is intended to constitute a waiver of the confidentiality of this message If the reader of this message is not the intended recipient or employeeagent of the intended recipient you are hereby notified that any duplication dissemination or distribution of this communication is unauthorized If you have received this document in error please notify the above office by telephone or by email immediately

RE Texas Set Meeting Jan nd and rd Cc PST Hey Shouldnt we all RSVP to Terri Wagnor Rita Original Message From mailto Sent Monday January AM To ROBESON DAVE Cc BREAKFIELD JAMES W BUCK KENNETH W WALLACE PAMELA H Subject RE Texas Set Meeting Jan nd and rd Again I apologize for the sending the notice so late We just got our wires crossedhopefully this wont happen in the future Regardless I beg that all will make an exception this time since most of you knew that we were planning on these dates Cary Reed Sr Business Standards Consultant audinet ROBESON DAVE AM To cc WALLACE PAMELA H BUCK KENNETH W BREAKFIELD JAMES W Subject RE Texas Set Meeting Jan nd and rd It is hard to get travel and hotel reservations with a one day notice Want to attend and participate but am not sure I can get there There are a lot of issues on the agenda Many of these probably have some material which could be provided up front so we can be prepared to reviewdiscuss Would it be possible to reschedule this for next week Dave Entergy Original Message From mailto Sent Monday January AM To Subject Texas Set Meeting Jan nd and rd First of all sorry for the late notice Heidi and I did not have our signals straight The next Texas Set meeting is scheduled for tomorrow Jan and Wednesday January rd in Austin at the ERCOT center room B The meeting is scheduled from on Tuesday and on Wednesday The agenda items are as follows Nominations for Chair and Vice Chair Proposed changes to Change Control process point to point contingency Final review of Review data gatherings findings Revist ERCOT validation of date in the past Change control and Tabled questions from Change control call CSA move inout gaps Texas Set rejection of response transactions at ERCOT Muni Coop transactions and Cary Reed Sr Business Standards Consultant audinet
